The paper deals with information leakage in a classical protocol computing the equality function in the SMP model, and demonstrates a quantum advantage in terms of information leakage for practical quantum protocols. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CC (computational complexity), cs.IT (information theory), cs.CR (cryptography and security), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.QI (quantum physics).
